<p align="center"><font color="#0E024D" face="Arial"><strong>PLAYER SUBMITTED STRATEGY</strong></font></p>
<div align="center"><center>

  <div align="center"><center><table border="0" width="90%">
    <tr>
      <td>
      <center><font face="Arial"><strong><b><font color="#800000">DRUIDS DON'T NEED POWERLEVELING :)</b></font> - <small>Hobbie, Mithaniel Marr</small></strong></font><font face="Arial"></center>
<div align="center"><center>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="80%">
  <tr>
    <td>
    <small><hr size="1" color="#C0C0C0"><P>
    Aside from a slump between 6-8 due to overcrowding, I've reached 14 in virtually record time using a few simple tricks. The best of them is called fear kiting, and it can be used on any animal ( I don't kill wolves and bears, they're amiable to us druids).
Simply put, snare an animal type appropriate for your level, and cast panic animal- both LOW level spells. Then just run along with the fleeing animal whacking away until the panic wears off, then back off and re-fear them. Learn the animals in the zones this works with- for example, I grabbed a tank in Oasis at 12th level to do the damage with, and started using this on yellow and red caimans- I made 14th the next night :) 
Next trick is to make sure you use whirling wind from a low level on up- Stinging Swarm you get at 14th and uses the same skill of conjuration, better have it up there or you'll burn mana all day on fizzles trying to swarm- I used WW religiously to pull from harmonied camps with until I got swarm, then just switched to burning. Lightning is not a really useful combat spell unless you have time to dump it- slow cast :( I'm checking Hail now but it doesn't look good. 
Nother trick is do not be shy casting shield of thistles on other ppl- use it for your tanks at every chance, it keeps the mob's attention on the tank and lets you safely dish out a few hits or heal them- plus we counted 90 some points of damage from the shield ALONE during a single fight last night- it certainly saved me some mana healing the tank :) It's also a safe way to help someone else win a fight if they're in trouble or you just want to help out- faster than you can say "Sure, I can powerlevel you to 14th guildbuddy! " you will have LOTS of friends to help you with quests :)
Will post some more when I learn it as I level :)
    </small></font></p>
    <p><small><font face="Arial">&nbsp;</font></small></td>
  </tr>
